12. Will not the Falling the Prices reduce the Wages of the Poor, and by that means make the Nation grow Rich, since Sir Jos. Child has very well observed, That where ever Wages are high, throughout the whole World, it is an infallible Evidence of the Riches of that Country;
                        Preface.
                        And where Wages for Labour runs low, 'tis a proof of the Poverty of that Place?
